value.value: A solid composed of active ingredient(s), excipients (usually electrolytes and bulking agents), and a solvent system which are lyophilized to yield a compressed solid with uniform ingredient distribution. The resulting lyophilized cake maintains its structure and stability over an extended period of time, and is intended for reconstitution prior to administration.
A substance composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s) in an anionic surfactant, for cleansing.
A solution or suspension composed of an anionic surfactant used for cleansing.
A solid bounded by a circular base converging upon a single vertex and intended for administration to the teeth and gingiva in the oral cavity.
A solid composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s) on a small piece of absorbent material attached to one end of a stick.
A solid composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s) in a soft, non-adhesive and absorbent piece of fabric or other material.
A film composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s).

A synthetic heptapeptide identical to endogenous angiotensin-(1-7) with vasodilator and antiproliferative activities. Therapeutic angiotensin 1-7 may inhibit cyclooxygenase 2 (COX-2) and the production of proinflammatory prostaglandins and may activate the angiotensin-(1-7) receptor Mas, resulting in diminished tumor cell proliferation. Activation of the angiotensin-(1-7) receptor Mas, a G-protein coupled, seven transmembrane protein, may down-regulate the phosphorylation and activation of Erk1 and Erk2 in the Erk1/Erk2 MAPK signaling pathway. In the renin-angiotensin system, the vasodilating activity of angiotensin- (1-7), hydrolysed from angiotensin II by the type I transmembrane metallopeptidase and carboxypeptidase angiotensin converting enzyme 2 (ACE2) in vivo, counteracts the vasoconstricting activity of angiotensin II.

A selective, orally active small molecule, targeting protein kinase B (PKB or AKT) and ribosomal protein S6 Kinase (p70S6K), with potential antineoplastic activity. XL418 inhibits the activities of PKB and p70S6K, both acting downstream of phosphoinosotide-3 kinase (PI3K). These kinases are often upregulated in a variety of cancers. Inhibition of PKB by this agent will induce apoptosis, while inhibition of p70S6K will result in the inhibition of translation within tumor cells.
A solution composed of a homogenous liquid that contains active and/or inert ingredient(s) dissolved in a suitable solvent or mixture of mutually miscible solvents.

label.value: Frozen Premix Intravenous Piggyback Solution Dosage Form

value.value: A solution that is reconstituted from a frozen pre-mixed form intended for intravenous administration simultaneously with an established compatible maintenance infusion drug by a mutual intravenous access.
A solution intended for intravenous administration simultaneously with an established compatible maintenance infusion drug by a mutual intravenous access.

A variant of Wilms tumor of the kidney characterized by the presence of cystic spaces separated by septa.  The septa contain immature epithelial cells, immature stromal cells, and blastema cells.  Surgical resection is usually curative.
A solution intended for administration into the intraperitoneal cavity.
A semi-solid, having a relatively thick consistency, intended for oral administration to facilitate ease of swallowing.
A solution that becomes a gelatinous liquid after administration.
A drug delivery system that includes a prefilled gel applicator.
A suspension composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s) that requires reconstitution and is intended oral administration.
A solid composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s) that resembles small, thin chips.

label.value: Powder Like Non-Effervescent Granule Dosage Form

value.value: A granule composed of a mixture of small (powder like), dry particles or grains, which does not have the ability to release gas upon contact with water.
A substance that requires reconstitution with a suitable solvent and is intended for oral administration in a drop-wise fashion.
A solution that requires reconstitution with a suitable solvent, and is intended for oral administration.

label.value: Suspension 12 Hour Sustained Release Dosage Form

value.value: A suspension designed to release active and/or inert ingredient(s) slowly so as to achieve a constant circulating concentration of the ingredient over a 12 hour time interval.
A preparation used in cleaning something.

A solid composed of an impermeable occlusive backing, a formulation matrix in which the active and/or inert ingredient(s) are dissolved or dispersed and an adhesive layer. It is intended for external application.
A suppository intended for administration within the rectum.

A usually benign tumor arising from the breast. It is characterized by the proliferation of cells with myoepithelial differentiation around spaces which are lined by epithelial cells. Rarely, the epithelial and/or myoepithelial cells may undergo malignant transformation. Cases with malignant transformation may follow an aggressive clinical course, including recurrences and local and distant metastases.
A suppository intended for administration within the vagina.

A solution or suspension distillate composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s) extracted from plant or animal matter and alcohol as the solvent and/or preservative. Fluid extract is prepared by percolation and subsequent evaporation such that the ingredient in each milliliter of the fluid extract is equivalent to 1 gram of the dried plant or animal derived matter.
A suspension intended for oral administration.
A suspension composed of a suspension that has been prepared immediately prior to dispensing or oral administration.
A solution intended for oral administration.
A suspension prepared immediately prior to dispensing or administration in a drop-wise fashion.
A suspension intended for administration to a body surface.
